# Blog posts (simple format)

Blog posts in `public/blog/` must use the **short, consistent format**. Reference: `public/blog/slow-flow-trails.md`.

## Required structure

1. **Title (H1)** — Sketch name only. No extra subtitle or tagline.
2. **Intro** — One short paragraph (1–3 sentences) describing the sketch.
3. **## Concept** — 3–5 bullet points on the idea and behavior.
4. **## Technical notes** — 2–4 short bullets on implementation.

## Do not include

- Long "Overview", "What Makes It Unique", or "Conclusion" sections.
- Code blocks or snippets.
- Subsections under Concept or Technical notes (e.g. "Core Techniques" with nested bullets).
- "Building Your Own", "Related Techniques", or multi-page prose.

Keep each post to one concise page: intro + Concept + Technical notes only.
